A motorist was killed and four others were injured in a head-on collision on the N1 outside De Doorns on Thursday morning, Western Cape traffic chief Kenny Africa said. Four passengers were injured. A Kia Picanto and a Nissan bakkie crashed into each other at around 06:00. ALSO READ: 13 killed after car and bakkie collide in horror West Rand crash Emergency services officials were still trying to free the body of the Kia driver, but the driver of the bakkie was freed, Africa said. Three passengers in the bakkie and one in the Kia were injured. The cause of the accident was not immediately clear. The collision occurred just a day before increased traffic on the roads for Easter.  (Supplied)  KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter  